    "This includes diversifying training datasets and refining model algorithms to identify and correct bias across modalities.TABLE I SUMMARY OF DATASETS, METRICS, AND BASELINE MODELS Component Details Purpose Datasets Aligned text, image, and audio Evaluate integration capability Metrics Accuracy, F1 score, Multimodal Integration Index Measure performance & integration Baselines State-of-the-art multimodal and single-task models Benchmark improvements TABLE II ACCURACY AND F1 SCORE COMPARISON Modality Metric Mistral 8x7B Baseline Model Text Accuracy 94.5% 89.2% Text F1 Score 93.8% 88.7% Image Accuracy 92.3% 86.5% Image F1 Score 91.9% 85.2% Audio Accuracy 91.1% 84.3% Audio F1 Score 90.7% 83.9%TABLE III MULTIMODAL INTEGRATION INDEX Modality Combination Mistral 8x7B Baseline Model Text-Image 89.3% 82.1% Text-Audio 87.7% 80.4% Image-Audio 88.5% 79.8% Text-Image-Audio 90.1% 83.5% D. Potential LimitationsWhile the modified Mistral 8x7B model shows substantial improvements in multimodal processing, there are inherent limitations to consider.",
    "The computational demand of processing large multimodal datasets is significant, which could limit scalability and real-time application.",
    "Additionally, the reliance on high-quality and well-aligned multimodal data for training may not always be feasible in less controlled environments.",
    "Addressing these limitations requires ongoing technological advancements and innovative approaches to data management and model training.",
    "E. Future Research DirectionsThe findings from this study open several avenues for future research."
